```
{
&quot;product-id&quot; : &quot;1&quot;
}
```


Now, it depends on your use-case, let&#39;s suppose in your case, `product-id` is keyword and fixed, and you just want to use the `exact search` or `aggregation` on the `product-id` field, and don&#39;t want the `full-text search`, than you better go with explicit mapping and define it as in `keyword` field, that way Elasticsearch storage and queries would be optimal. You can refer to this [Stackoverflow comment][1], for more information on it.

**Bottomline, When you want to have a greater control on how your data should be indexed, It&#39;s always better to define explicit mapping than relaying on default mapping generated by Elasticsearch.**


